  "decision_conditions": [
    "<div>The scale and design of the balcony would present an increased feeling of overlooking and loss of privacy within the rear gardens of the nieghbouring properties, especially no.40 Beamway , therefore constituting unneighbourly development and contrary to:<br></div><div><br></div><div><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nNational Planning Policy Framework </span>(NPPF) (DLUHC, December 2023)</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- Policy\r\nD4 of the London Plan (March 2021);</span><o:p></o:p></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- Policy\r\nCP3 of </span>Local Development Framework (LDF) Core Strategy (July 2010)<o:p></o:p></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nPolicies BP8 and BP11 of the </span>Local Development Framework (LDF) Borough\r\nWide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011)<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- The Residential\r\nExtensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012);<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nPolicies SP2, DMD1 and DMD6 of </span>The London Borough of Barking and\r\nDagenham’s Draft Local Plan: (Regulation 19 Main Modifications Version, February 2024)<o:p></o:p></p></div>",
    "<div>The scale, siting and design of the balcony would add undesirbale bulk and mass to the rear dormer and would present a jarring uncharacteristic feature creating a fragmented appearance, at odds to the character and design of the uniform and distinctive built form of Beamway and the wider area. As such, the proposed development is contrary to:<br></div><div><br></div><div><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nNational Planning Policy Framework</span>&nbsp;(NPPF) (DLUHC, December 2023)</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- Policy D4 of the\r\nLondon Plan (March 2021)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- Policy\r\nCP3 of the </span>Local Development Framework (LDF) Core Strategy (July 2010)<o:p></o:p></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nPolicies BP8 and BP11 of the </span>Local Development Framework (LDF) Borough\r\nWide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011)<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- The Residential\r\nExtensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nPolicies SP2, DMD1 and DMD6 of </span>The London Borough of Barking and\r\nDagenham’s Draft Local Plan: (Regulation 19 Main Modifications Version, February 2024)</p></div>"
